<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="dead-adj">dead <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ded/    美 /ded/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>死的；无生命的；(植物) 枯萎的 ：</strong></h4>
<p>反 alive </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the dead 
死者</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She has been dead for one year. 
她去世已经一年了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>drop dead</strong> (= die suddenly)
猝死；暴毙</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>dead flowers 
枯萎的花</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>麻木的；冷淡的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My arm’s gone dead. 
我的手臂麻木了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>in a dead voice 
用冷淡的语气</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>无生气的；寂静的；死气沉沉的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>in the dead hours of the night 
在夜深人静时</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>不工作的；已废弃的；已使用过的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The battery is dead. 
电池没电了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a dead volcano 
死火山</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.<strong>完全的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>(a) dead silence (= in complete silence)
死寂；完全安静</p></div></div>